    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a museum-grade example of Japanese performance engineering. At its heart is the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting perfect compression across all faces and a vacuum system that holds steady at factory specifications. The drivetrain features the original 5-speed short-throw transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, providing immediate power delivery without gear whine or lash. The aluminum double-wishbone suspension remains tight, preserving the car's neutral handling characteristics and 50/50 weight distribution. This chassis is completely free of oxidation, with original paint depth readings consistent across all panels. Inside, the driver-centric cockpit is immaculate, featuring an uncracked dashboard and pristine bolster integrity on the high-grip buckets. This is a turn-key investment for the collector who demands mechanical purity and aesthetic perfection",
      "price": 50000.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 10
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
